<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/277</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé d’Affaires in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-07T14:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Your telegram of August 6, 8 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d287fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> Report nationality and numbers of troops withdrawn
                            from the railway and of those remaining. Has the Diplomatic Corps
                            recently discussed question of continuing railway guards? Have
                            governments withdrawing made any arrangements with other powers for
                            substitutes?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>